      {
        "parentPluginId": "@kbn/i18n",
        "id": "def-common.getLocaleLabel",
        "type": "Function",
        "tags": [],
        "label": "getLocaleLabel",
        "description": [
          "\nReturns the friendly label for a locale id, using `Intl.DisplayNames`\nin the **endonym** pattern: each locale is rendered in its own\nlanguage (`fr-FR` → `\"français\"`, `ja-JP` → `\"日本語\"`). This means a\nuser stuck in a language they cannot read still sees their preferred\nlanguage listed in a script they recognise.\n\nRegion is dropped before lookup so the label is the bare language\nname, following each language's own orthographic conventions (French\ndoes not capitalise language names; English and German do).\n\nFalls back to the locale id when `Intl.DisplayNames` is unavailable\n(e.g., minimal-ICU Node builds) or cannot resolve the locale."
        ],
        "signature": [
          "(id: string) => string"
        ],
        "path": "src/platform/packages/shared/kbn-i18n/src/locales.ts",
